   And thatвҖҷs it: call вҺ•DLX to get the solution(s).  In general all
problems that can be solved by вҺ•DLX contain 3 steps:

   вҖў translate the problem into a constraints matrix B,
   вҖў ZвҶҗвҺ•DLX B, and
   вҖў translate the result Z back into the problem domain.

   Another application of вҺ•DLX is solving sudokus.  The constraints
matrix is a little more complicated, but the principle is the same.  GNU
APL is shipped with two workspaces: sudoku.apl (which solves sudokus
without using вҺ•DLX) and sudoku_DLX.apl (which solves sudokus using
вҺ•DLX).


