   A new feature of вҺ•FIO (which is not available with the native
function FILE_IO) is вҺ•FIO[49].  вҺ•FIO[49] is a monadic operator which
takes a monadic conversion function as function argument.  For example:

     ZвҶҗF вҺ•FIO[49] 'filename'

   reads the file named filename line by line.  For every line read, the
conversion function F is called and the result returned by F is enclosed
and stored in Z. In other words,

     ZвҶҗF вҺ•FIO[49] 'filename'

   does:

     Z FВЁZвҶҗвҺ•FIO[49] 'filename'


