2.27 вҺ•FFT - Fast Fourier Transform
==================================

For those interested in signal processing and the like, GNU APL provides
вҺ•FFT:

   The monadic form вҺ•FFT B is a shortcut for the dyadic form 0 вҺ•FFT B.
It computes the FFT of complex or real B without applying a window
function.

   The dyadic form A вҺ•FFT B provides more control over what вҺ•FFT
computes.  A is an integer scalar which falls into one of three ranges.

   The first range from ВҜ15 to ВҜ10 does not compute an FFT, but returns
the result of multiplying B with one of several window functions, that
are frequently used in the context of FFTs.  The result has same shape
as B and can be used for analyzing or troubleshooting FFTs:

   вҖў A=ВҜ10: no FFT, return the Hann window applied to B
   вҖў A=ВҜ11: no FFT, return the Hamming window applied to B
   вҖў A=ВҜ12: no FFT, return the Blackman window applied to B
   вҖў A=ВҜ13: no FFT, return the Blackman-Harris window applied to B
   вҖў A=ВҜ14: no FFT, return the Blackman-Nuttal window applied to B
   вҖў A=ВҜ15: no FFT, return the Flat-Top window applied to B

   The second range around 0 contains the computation of the forward and
inverse FFTs:

   вҖў 0 вҺ•FFT B returns the "normal" (aka.  forward) FFT of the numeric
     array B.
   вҖў ВҜ1 вҺ•FFT B returns the inverse FFT of the numeric array B.

   The third range from 10 to 15 corresponds to the first range and
first multiplies B with a window function and then computes the FFT:

   вҖў A=10: FFT(B Г— Hann window)
   вҖў A=11: FFT(B Г— Hamming window)
   вҖў A=12: FFT(B Г— Blackman window)
   вҖў A=13: FFT(B Г— Blackman-Harris window)
   вҖў A=14: FFT(B Г— Blackman-Nuttal window)
   вҖў A=15: FFT(B Г— Flat-Top window)

   вҚҙвҚҙB can be 1 (one-dimensional FFT, the most common case) or more.
The implementation of вҺ•FFT uses libfftw3, aka.  "The fastest Fourier
Transform in the West."  GNU APL checks the presence of libfftw3 when it
is ./configureвҖҷd.  If libfftw3 is present then вҺ•FFT will hopefully
return the expected result; if not then a DOMAIN ERROR will be raised
when вҺ•FFT is used.

   вҺ•FFT honors the presence of /etc/fftw/wisdom (see man fftw-wisdom) to
speed up the computations performed by вҺ•FFT. Creating /etc/fftw/wisdom
will take a few hours, though, so that creating it will not pay off for
most mortals.


