2.30 вҺ•MAP - Map Value
=====================

вҺ•MAP changes the ravel items of its right argument according to a
mapping table provided as its left argument.  Let ZвҶҗA вҺ•MAP B.

   The left argument A of ZвҶҗA вҺ•MAP B shall be a NГ—2 matrix.  Each
2-element row of A, say A[J;], specifies a separate mapping A[J;1] вҶ’
A[J;2].  The result Z has the same shape as the right argument B. The
items Z[...]  of their result are constructed from their corresponding
items B[...]  in B as follows:

   вҖў if B[...]  вүЎ A[J;1] for some J then Z[...]  is A[J;2].

   вҖў otherwise B[...]  is different from all A[1;J] and then Z[...]  is
     B[...]

   In other words, Z is B, but with items of B found in A[;1] replaced
by their mapped item A[;2].

   In practice the left argument A is frequently created from a literal
APL value such as 5 2вҚҙвҖҷeEwWaAzZ92вҖҷ in the example below.  To simplify
these cases, A вҺ•MAP B also accepts a vector instead of a NГ—2 matrix:

   A вҺ•MAP B вҶҗвҶ’ ((N 2)вҚҙA) вҺ•MAP B if (2Г—N) вҶҗвҶ’ вҚҙA

   Examples:

      вҚқ the map A
      вҠўAвҶҗ5 2вҚҙ'eEwWaAzZ92'
eE    вҚқ map 'e' вҶ’ 'E'
wW    вҚқ map 'w' вҶ’ 'W'
aA    вҚқ map 'a' вҶ’ 'A'
zZ    вҚқ map 'z' вҶ’ 'Z'
92    вҚқ map '9' вҶ’ '2'

      вҚқ the value B being mapped
      вҠўBвҶҗ'Halloween'
Halloween

      вҚқ the result of A вҺ•MAP B
      A вҺ•MAP B
HAlloWEEn

      AвҶҗ'eEwWaAzZ92'   вҚқ vector A instead of NГ—2 matrix
      A вҺ•MAP B
HAlloWEEn


   NOTES:
   вҖў The keys of the mapping A (i.e.  the elements in column A[;1]) must
     be unique.  If they are not then the mapping is ambiguous and a
     DOMAIN ERROR is raised.

   вҖў Nested items in B: if an item of B is nested, then it is either
     equal to some (also nested) key, say A[N;1], (in that case it is
     being mapped to A[N;2] in the result), or it is different from all
     keys in A[;1] (and in that case the corresponding item in the
     result is the item in B.

   вҖў Nested items in A: if a key, say A[N;1], is nested and matches an
     equal (hence also nested) item in B, then the corresponding item in
     the result will be A[N;2] (which may or may not be nested).  If a
     (nested or not nested) key A[N;1] is equal to an item in B, then
     the corresponding item in the result will be nested if A[N;2] is
     nested.  If, for some N, the depths of A[N;1] and A[N;2] differ,
     then depths of B and A вҺ•MAP B may differ as well.  That is, вҺ•MAP
     conserves the shape of B, but not necessarily the depth of B.

   вҖў By default the mapping of B is non-recursive, i.e.  the top-level
     items of B are compared with the top-level keys A[;1], and nested
     keys and items of B are handled as described above.

     Sometimes, however, it is desirable to recursively descend into the
     nested sub-values of B (though never of A). This can be achieved by
     enclosing A as shown in the examples below.

      AвҶҗ5 2вҚҙ'eEwWaAzZ92'
      BвҶҗ'Hal' 'low' 'een'   вҚқ nested B
      4 вҺ•CR A вҺ•MAP B        вҚқ non-recursive (none of the keys in A[;1] matches)
в”ҸвҶ’в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”“
в”ғв”ҸвҶ’в”Ғв”Ғв”“ в”ҸвҶ’в”Ғв”Ғв”“ в”ҸвҶ’в”Ғв”Ғв”“в”ғ
в”ғв”ғHalв”ғ в”ғlowв”ғ в”ғeenв”ғв”ғ
в”ғв”—в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”ӣ в”—в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”ӣ в”—в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”ӣв”ғ
