2.34 вҺ•PS - Print Style
======================

вҺ•PS is an integer vector that currently (read: as of SVN 982) contains
two integers which control some details of how APL values are printed.
The default value of вҺ•PS is 0 0.  вҺ•PS is a session variable which
survives the *)LOAD*ing of workspaces.

   вҺ•PS[1] = 0: print rational quotients as normal floating point numbers
(digits, fractional point, possibly an exponent).

   вҺ•PS[1] = 1: print rational quotients as NumeratorГ·Denominator.

   Note: вҺ•PS[1] has no effect if rational numbers were not
./configureвҖҷd.

   вҺ•PS[2] = 0: no "boxing" of APL values

   вҺ•PS[2] > 0: "boxing" of APL values according to вҺ•PS[2].

   Setting вҺ•PS[2] has the same effect as the debug command ]BOXING and
uses the same values.

   Note: For compatibility with older workspaces, assigning a single
value to вҺ•PS assigns that value to вҺ•PS[2] and sets вҺ•PS[1] to 0.


