2.37 вҺ•SQL - SQL Database Interface
==================================

вҺ•SQL was kindly contributed by Elias MГҘrtenson.

   As of GNU APL 1.6, the native function SQL has been replaced by the
system function вҺ•SQL, described below.  вҺ•SQL has an axis argument that
selects a sub-function of вҺ•SQL.

2.37.1 вҺ•SQL[0] : display subfunctions
-------------------------------------

      вҺ•SQL[0]''
Available function numbers:
type  вҺ•SQL[1] file      - open a database file, return reference ID for it
      вҺ•SQL[2] ref       - close database
query вҺ•SQL[3,db] params - send SQL query
query вҺ•SQL[4,db] params - send SQL update
      вҺ•SQL[5] ref       - begin a transaction
      вҺ•SQL[6] ref       - commit current transaction
      вҺ•SQL[7] ref       - rollback current transaction
      вҺ•SQL[8] ref       - list tables
ref   вҺ•SQL[9] table     - list columns for table
      вҺ•SQL[10] type     - return the library version number
      вҺ•SQL[11] type     - return the library version string

2.37.2 ref вҶҗ A вҺ•SQL[1] B : open database
----------------------------------------

      type  вҺ•SQL[1] file

   Connect to database of type A using connection arguments B. The
result is a database handle ref to be used in the other вҺ•SQL functions.

   A must be a string indicating the database type.  Currently supported
values are вҖҷpostgresqlвҖҷ and вҖҷsqliteвҖҷ.

   B is the connection parameters which depends on the type of database:

   - For typeвүЎвҖҷsqliteвҖҷ: the argument is string pointing to the database
file.

   - For typeвүЎвҖҷpostgresqlвҖҷ, the argument is a standard connect string as
described in the PostgreSQL documentation.

   This function returns a database handle that should be used when
using other SQL functions.  This value should be seen as an opaque
handle.  It is, however, guaranteed that the handle is a scalar value.

2.37.3 вҺ•SQL[2] B : close database
---------------------------------

      вҺ•SQL[2] ref

   Disconnect from database ref.

   B is the database handle that should be disconnected.  After this
function has been called, no further operations are to be performed on
this handle.  Future calls to вҺ•SQL[1] may reuse previously disconnected
handles.

2.37.4 Z вҶҗ A вҺ•SQL[3, ref] B : database query (with result)
----------------------------------------------------------

      query вҺ•SQL[3, ref] params

   Execute a select statement and return the result table.

   The axis parameter indicates the database handle.

   A is a select statement to be executed.  Positional parameters can be
supplied by specifying a question mark "?"  in the statement.

   B is an array containing the values for the positional parameters.
If the array is of rank 2, the statement will be executed multiple times
with each row being the values for each call.

   The return value Z is a rank-2 array representing the result of the
select statement.  Null values are returned as вҚ¬ and empty strings are
returned as вҖқ.

2.37.5 Z вҶҗ A вҺ•SQL[4, ref] B : database query (w/o result)
---------------------------------------------------------

      query вҺ•SQL[4, ref] params

   Execute an SQL statement that does not return a result.

   This function is identical to SQLвҲҶSelect with the exception that it
is used on statements which do not return a result table.

2.37.6 вҺ•SQL[5] B : start transaction
------------------------------------

      вҺ•SQL[5] ref

   Begin a transaction.

2.37.7 вҺ•SQL[6] B : commit transaction
-------------------------------------

      вҺ•SQL[6] ref

   Commit a transaction.

2.37.8 вҺ•SQL[7] B : rollback transaction
---------------------------------------

      вҺ•SQL[7] ref

   Rolls back the current transaction.

2.37.9 ZвҶҗвҺ•SQL[8] B : table names
--------------------------------

      вҺ•SQL[8] ref

   Return an array containing the name of all tables.

2.37.10 ZвҶҗвҺ•SQL[9] B : column names
----------------------------------

      ref  вҺ•SQL[9] table

   Return an array containing information about the columns in the given
table.  Currently, the column layout is as follows:

   Name Type

   More columns containing additional information may be added in a
future release.

2.37.11 Z вҶҗ вҺ•SQL[10] B : library version number
-----------------------------------------------

Return the version number (integer scalar) of the library that was used
to implement the database type B.

2.37.12 Z вҶҗ вҺ•SQL[11] B : library version string
-----------------------------------------------

Return the version string of the library that was used to implement the
database type B.


