2.40.6 XML Queries
------------------

The different functions in dyadic вҺ•XML are intended to construct XML
queries.  An XML query extracts information from, or modifies
information in, an XML document.  XML queries may differ considerably in
their details, but usually follow these top-level steps:

  1. Read an XML document into, say, APL (APLвҶҗ0 вҺ•XML B or APLвҶҗ1 вҺ•XML B)
  2. Optionally, display the structure of the document (3, 4, or 5 вҺ•XML
     APL)
  3. Select a subset of XML nodes (= GNU APL member names, 6 вҺ•XML APL)
  4. retrieve or modify the data in the selected XML nodes (with
     something like MEMBERSвҶҗ(вҠӮAPL) FUNВЁ6вҺ•XML APLвҶҗвҺ•XML followed by
     MEMBERвҠғ )
  5. Optionally, convert the modified XML document back to XML (0 вҺ•XML
     APL)


